      "question": "In a bag, there are coins of 25p, 10p, and 5p denominations in ratio 1:2:3. If there are Rs. 30 in all, how many 5p coins are there?",
      "options": [
        "50",
        "100",
        "150",
        "200"
      ],
      "correctAnswer": "150",
      "explanation": "Let coins be x,2x,3x. 25x+20x+15x=3000p. 60x=3000, x=50. 5p coins=3×50=150."
